PRESIDENT Samia Suluhu Hassan is expected to grace the National Heroes Day celebrations set for July 25 this year in Dodoma Capital. Prime Minister Kassim Majaliwa revealed that on Saturday when he inspected preparations for the event at Mashujaa grounds in Dodoma. The PM said that he is satisfied with the preparations done by the national festival and state celebrations committee in collaboration with defence and security organs. "The celebrations of Heroes Day will be marked at national level in Dodoma region and will be graced by President Samia and Zanzibar President Dr Hussein Mwinyi.  Retired national leaders   will also attend the celebrations," Majaliwa said. Majaliwa said that President Samia had approved the celebrations to be held in Dodoma at national level but also directing to be held at regional level across the country by visiting various memorial sites in respective regions. "The committee has done a good job by cooperating with defence and security organs, I am satisfied with the preparations including the area, various entertainment groups ... this year Immigration Force has started officially   to participate in parade," he said. The  Premier also commended the  media   on how  it has played its part  in  encouraging wananchi to take part  in various  national  events,  noting that  the government values  their contributions. "The government is pleased  on how people are turning up  in national events ... we believe that  they will also turn up in large number during Heroes Day  celebrations," he said. The Heroes Day is traditionally marked on every July 25 to honour soldiers who fought for the country.